definition.value: A glycosylglycerol that is  1-O-(D-glucosyl)glycerol in which the secondary hydroxy group of the glycerol moiety has been converted into the corresponding L-fucopyranoside.
The S-malonyl derivative of coenzyme A.
A glycosylmannose consisting of an alpha-D-mannopyranose residue and a D-mannopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
A long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of myristic acid.
A medium-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of octanoic acid.
An octadecenoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of oleic acid.
An amino disaccharide consisting of alpha-L-fucopyranose and 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of oxalic acid.
